  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 520 mg
cuisine: Mediterranean
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise, sliced into ½-inch-thick half-moons). Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced).

Pat @skin-on salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add salmon and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer salmon to one side of a #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken or salmon for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through, 5-6 minutes per side, or cook salmon (skin sides down) until skin is crisp, 5-7 minutes, then flip and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more. Turn off heat; transfer to a cutting board. Wipe out pan.

Toss zucchini with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper on opposite side of baking sheet with salmon.

Roast on top rack until salmon is cooked through and zucchini is lightly browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Toss and roast zucchini as instructed (skip roasting chicken or salmon!).

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

When pasta has 5 minutes left, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for salmon over medium heat. Add tomato and garlic; cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Whisk in ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings), @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

> Use pan used for chicken or salmon here.

Add drained spaghetti, zucchini, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, a splash of reserved pasta cooking water, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} to pan with sauce; toss to combine.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Slice salmon crosswise.

Divide spaghetti between plates; top with salmon and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Serve.

> Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon!).

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.